H4832  
מרפּא  
מַרפֵּא ‎ marpê‘  
*mar-pay‘*  
From [7495](h7495) properly *curative*, that is, literally (concretely.md)
a *medicine*, or (abstractly) a *cure*; figuratively (concretely)
*deliverance*, or (abstractly) *placidity: -* (\[in-\]) cure (-able),
healing (-lth), remedy, sound, wholesome, yielding.  
